observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:

instruct the Bids and Awards Committee to submit an explanation on why the projects were awarded to the winning bidders despite the submission of tax clearances that can be considered spurious and why the said transactions should not be disallowed in audit;

require the Bids and Awards Committee to verify all documents submitted by bidders and ensure that they are eligible, prior to award of the projects/contracts.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:

instruct the Municipal Accountant to establish the correctness of the said short remittance and reclassify the recorded Advances for Operating Expenses of P140,218.75 to Due from Officers and Employees;

require the Municipal Agriculturist to immediately settle the said shortage.
